AB  - Background: Advanced practice registered nurses perceive training in chest X-ray (CXR) interpretation as inadequate to practice with competency. Methods: Gamification was used to teach CXR interpretation to adult gerontology acute care nurse practitioner learners. After didactic instruction, learners participated in a series of online CXR questions. Results: At post-assessment, n = 28 learners were either somewhat (85.7%, n = 24) or very (10.7%, n = 3) confident in making correct diagnoses. Additionally, 64.3% of the learners answered at least 75% of questions correctly, indicating knowledge retention. Conclusion: Learners gained confidence and retained knowledge in CXR interpretation in an engaging format. (c) 2025 Elsevier Inc. All rights are reserved, including those for text and data mining, AI training, and similar technologies.
