AB  - With the rapid escalation of cyber threats across industries, strengthening cybersecurity awareness has become a global priority. Traditional Security Education, Training, and Awareness (SETA) programs often struggle to engage users and drive lasting behavioral change. Gamification-applying game design elements such as incentives, challenges, narratives, and interactivity in non-game contexts-offers a promising alternative. By enhancing cybersecurity learning, gamification can enhance knowledge retention, motivation, and proactive security behaviors. This paper examines cybersecurity awareness and training advancements over the past five years, highlighting effective frameworks, tools, and sector-specific applications. It also identifies critical gaps, such as limited personalization, fragmented evaluation metrics, and inadequate integration with emerging technologies. In conclusion, the study outlines future strategies, such as leveraging artificial intelligence, blockchain, and adaptive feedback mechanisms to advance gamified cybersecurity training and foster stronger human defenses within modern cybersecurity systems.
