AB  - This paper introduces a newly developed compact CAN bus training system, to bridge the gap between theoretical knowledge and practical application in engineering education. The system incorporates a real BMW e46 instrument cluster into a tabletop training device, facilitating direct interaction with CAN bus technology. Through a two-phase development process involving literature review and practical adaptation, the system was designed to enhance student engagement and understanding by providing hands-on experience with traditional software like Vector CANoe. Preliminary classroom evaluations indicate a marked improvement in students' comprehension and interest. This approach demonstrates that real-world applications can significantly enhance learning outcomes compared to simulations. Future research will explore the long-term effects of this hands-on educational method on knowledge retention.
