AB  - Modern language education requires flexible, intelligent platforms that can adapt to diverse learning needs while maintaining accessibility. Web-based smart teaching systems present an ideal solution, offering device-independent access and centralized management of educational resources. However, current implementations often face limitations in personalization accuracy, real-time interaction quality, and adaptive content delivery, resulting in suboptimal learning experiences. To overcome these challenges, this study develops an intelligent system combining knowledge graph-enhanced recommendation Transformer-Based Adaptive Learning Model (TALM), algorithms with real-time performance analytics. The solution employs a hybrid approach integrating collaborative filtering (98.2% accuracy) and deep neural networks (97.6% prediction precision) to deliver personalized learning paths. System evaluation demonstrates outstanding metrics: content recommendation relevance (96.9%), response latency (98.4% requests processed < 0.3s), knowledge retention improvement (95.8%), and user engagement rates (97.1%). The system successfully merges web technology's accessibility with advanced AI-driven personalization, creating a robust framework for English language education. Its consistently high-performance metrics confirm effectiveness in addressing critical gaps in digital language learning while maintaining the flexibility required for varied educational contexts. This approach establishes a new standard for intelligent, web-based teaching systems that dynamically respond to learner needs.
