AB  - The use of immersive technologies compared to traditional methods of anatomy education has the potential to enhance student's spatial awareness and improve knowledge retention on anatomy topics. However, research investigating the use and effectiveness of such technologies as part of the anatomy curricula is still limited. Therefore, this study aimed to evaluate the experiences and efficiency of an AR mobile application (Anat_Hub) as a learning and motivational tool in anatomy education, particularly of the musculoskeletal system, using the attention, relevance, confidence, and satisfaction (ARCS) model. The study used a mixed method approach that entailed using both qualitative and quantitative questions to obtain, analyse, and interpret the data, to evaluate student experience and motivation with the immersive anatomy mobile learning tool. The AR anatomy application learning tool was shown to effectively produce higher motivation and could improve engagement and understanding of the anatomy content.
